Talks of an Activision buyback have gone nowhere, at least for the moment. "We think that reports of the two sides failing to reach agreement on price are close to the mark," analyst Michael Pachter has said in the past, but the question remains: would Vivendi accept any offer Kotick might make, or would it rather keep a stranglehold on its golden goose?
